About this item

  • GAMEPLAY: Teams of two square off to see who can guess the secret Password first. Communicate wisely because players can give only one-word clues, and the fewer the clues the higher the score!
  • DETAILS: This game includes 50 Password Cards, Scoring Indicator Dial, Score Pad, 2 Magic Window Revealers, and Instructions, so youll be ready to play for years to come.
  • GAME NIGHT: Password is the fun party game where you get your team to guess the Secret Password using one word clues! Its for 3 or more players ages 10 years old and up.
  • PLAY AT PARTIES: The rules are easy to learn and the game is difficult to stop playing, its that much fun! For game nights, this family friendly game is perfect for kids, teens, and adults.
  • ENDLESS GAMES: Endless Games presents card, dice, party, word, trivia, survey, and pop culture games for everyone! Youll find high quality games that are easy to learn and provide endless play value.

        How customer reviews and ratings work

        Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

        To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

        4.0 out of 5 stars Great family game!
        Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2023
        Verified Purchase
        I grew up watching Password on TV in the 60s...and I think this is where American audiences fell in love with Betty White, whose husband Allan Ludden was the longtime host. I used to play it all the time as a young person. So when I was looking for a gift for our family "white elephant" at Christmas I knew this would be perfect because even the 6 and 9 year old could play it - our family loves board games so I usually give a game for my contribution. Interestingly enough, my husband picked this gift as a steal, so it came back. to me, LOL.

        The words included in this game are challenging and we had a blast with it. It was also a great device to settle down some lively grandchildren during large family events...everything became so quiet once we started playing.

        The only reason I gave it 4 stars on the overall rating is that the word cards - on which the text is camouflaged until you put it in the blue-tinted holder - is hard to read so that should be corrected by the manufacturer. Otherwise, it's a winner!
